				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/quikngruvn" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(333389); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=333389&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610250842" alt="Quikngruvn" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=333389)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/quikngruvn" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(333389); return false;" >Quikngruvn</a></span> <span class="odate time_1266184179 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">14 Feb 2010 21:49</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-699639">
									

<p>Oh, this I like. Nice way to take a classic WTF? and turn it into Holy Sh-! But, a technical nitpick: <a href="/scp-120">SCP-120</a> wouldn't work like that. Only conscious humans carrying less than 37.8&nbsp;kg of stuff can go through 120, and I assume 173s in metal containers weigh more than 83 pounds. (Well, I guess they <em>could</em> weigh less, but that seems awfully unlikely.)</p>
<p>What to use instead, though? <a href="/scp-004">SCP-004</a> comes to mind, but it's a fixed location. Chuck 'em into <a href="/scp-094">SCP-094</a>? Feed 'em to <a href="/scp-101">SCP-101</a> (if they even fit)? Maybe something else I can't think of….</p>
<p>But y'know, in the end it's just a minor pedantic issue that won't stop me from upvoting.</p>

							</div>

								
					
